{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1784516728,"nonce":"/IxRLaEN0rK32jATIdkDat9VmIE=","message":"Phase 3 PR 6 (PostgreSQL materialized views, body) MERGED — PR #116, squash 45a4474. Adds a materialized flag on ViewModel so matviews reuse the whole regular-view machinery (structural body, view-to-view dependency ordering, ordered_views, KDL, PG body introspection) with branches only where DDL diverges. PG render: CREATE MATERIALIZED VIEW AS ... WITH DATA / DROP MATERIALIZED VIEW; a matview has no CREATE OR REPLACE so any change (or a regular-materialized transition) drops and re-creates it. PG introspect: relkind m alongside v, body via pg_get_viewdef, a view/matview may depend on either. New SchemaCapabilities.materialized_views (PG true, MySQL/SQLite false) rejects a matview on create, on an incremental drop, and (SQLite) as a collateral view in the desired model. Comments canonicalized away (no backend renders/introspects a view comment) so a commented matview does not churn destructively (also in the offline package-diff path). SAFETY: squealy models only the body, and a change re-creates it, so a matview carrying anything a recreate would reset is REFUSED rather than silently stripped — the full ALTER MATERIALIZED VIEW storage/stats grammar: indexes (incl. a UNIQUE index for REFRESH CONCURRENTLY), reloptions + toast.* options, a tablespace or access method differing from the effective session default, and per-column SET STORAGE/COMPRESSION/STATISTICS/(n_distinct). Contract: a scalar squealy-authored matview publish-introspect-replan-empty, live-tested (disable-to-fail on the materialized round-trip). codex 8 rounds to CLEAN; bounded findings fixed with tests, the recreate-data-loss risk became a loud grammar-complete reject. Epic STAYS OPEN. Follow-up 91c061f = PR 7 (model matview indexes + storage so they round-trip instead of being rejected; reader/forward-authoring invertibility). Ph